                    <span>I really enjoyed the book, Where I'd like to be. It had alot of truth behind the story line, it used alot of real life situations. The young girl Maddie had a very inteligent mind and view on life. I also really enjoyed the book because you could actually step into Maddies life and her experiances around her.
<br />
<br />The worst part of the whole book would have to be when you find out that Madiie really does have family but the can't take care of her the way a young girl would need to be taken care of. The best part of the book was when the younge children completed there tree house it turned out great. The book had alot of up and down scenes  it kept you quessing but never left you hanging.
<br />
<br />One story element was when Maddie explains her meeting the the ghost of an elderly man when she was a baby. She explains that the ghost saved her life while at her grandmothers house. She explains that the ghost forced her grandma to awaken and find Maddie tangled up in her blanket fighting for air. Another story elemt is when Logan, Maddie, Murphy, and Ricky Ray go to the lumber yard for supplies for there tree house. They had know way to carry it so the owner of the lumber yard carried to the to logans house where they would constructed the house. They had the tree house up and running in little under a week.</span>
                  
