                    <span>This is a great book about friendship. It is a fiction book. It is by Frances O'Roark Dowell.
<br />Some of the things that I like about this book are when Maddie's granny, Ganny Lane, says that when Maddie was an infant she was saved by a ghost. I also like it when Maddie, Ricky Ray, Logan Parish, and Murphy try to build a fort because they are accomplishing a dream together. Another reason I like this book is because it shows true friendship and how people forgive each other.
<br />I would recommend this book to anybody who likes a good fiction book. I would also say that it is more of a young adult book because of some of the vocabulary and events.
<br /></span>
                  
